%I A397735 #6 Jul 08 2026 10:48:28
%S A397735 1,2,2,4,2,8,4,10,10,22,6,74,12,156,168
%N A397735 Number of regular integral graphs on n vertices.
%C A397735 A (simple, undirected) graph is called integral if all eigenvalues of its adjacency matrix are integers.
%C A397735 For regular graphs, integrality is equivalent to Laplacian integrality (i.e., all eigenvalues of its Laplacian matrix are integers).
%H A397735 N. Johnston, S. Plosker, and L. M. B. Varona, <a href="https://doi.org/10.48550/arXiv.2607.06336">Enumeration of Laplacian integral and {-1,0,1}-diagonalizable graphs</a>, arXiv:2607.06336 [math.CO], 2026.
%H A397735 L. M. B. Varona, <a href="https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.21114288">Small {-1,0,1}-Diagonalizable Graphs: A Computational Survey</a>, Zenodo, 2026.
%e A397735 For n = 4, the only four regular integral graphs are K_4, C_4, 2*K_2, and 4*K_1, so a(4) = 4.
%Y A397735 Cf. A005176 (number of regular graphs).
%Y A397735 Cf. A064731 (number of connected integral graphs).
%Y A397735 Cf. A077027 (number of integral graphs).
%Y A397735 Cf. A363064 (number of connected Laplacian integral graphs).
%Y A397735 Cf. A363065 (number of Laplacian integral graphs).
%K A397735 nonn,hard,more
%O A397735 1,2
%A A397735 _Nathaniel Johnston_, Jul 08 2026
